{
  "stem": "12053.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were going dirt cheap in Coventry, because nobody wanted to live in Coventry.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was wartime.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she'd bought another house in-- already to install my parents as housekeepers. so they could earn their keep there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was already sorted out months before that my parents came.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they gave the permission for my parents to come, you see, although it was the Coventry Cathedral which sponsored my sister and which sponsored us.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they got on the wrong-- they got the wrong caliber of people.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They weren't going to work in a-- in somebody's boarding house.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the night-- I don't think-- that was the only time in my life I ever fainted.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I've been through tragedies, terrible tragedies, in my life.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I lost my only son at the age of 21.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't faint.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had to look after my family.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I had to take it and carry on living.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But that time, when my parents came, there was such a god almighty row.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was so tremendous when my parents found out what had happened to their children.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They didn't find out the real thing, you know, the, the terror I lived in from Uncle Billy.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That they never found out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He would have killed him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father would have killed him, although he never succeeded.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they found out how we lived, how, how, how terrified we were, how hungry we  were, and the work that went on day and night out in the, in the factory for my brother, and for me, the housework and the factory and the cotton mill job.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was such a row.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my parents couldn't speak English.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my father, without speaking any English, went to the village-- it was a village-- to the telephone.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
